Session-6: Unit Volume Management
=================================
Q) What are Kubernetes volumes?
 =>  Kubernetes provides various volume plug-ins that can be mounted inside the container to store some data temporarily or in a persistent manner, or locally as well.

Q) What is remote storage?
 => Remote storage can be the Cloud volume plug-ins, GlusterFs, and NFS. All these can be created as remote storage.
 => You have external storage outside of your Gluster, and your data can be saved over there. So even if the Gluster goes down, your data is still safe.

Q) What is ephemeral storage?
 =>
We have two way to provision volume in k8s.
  1) Static (Not use in compines these days)
  2) Dynamic (Mostly in use)
      => PV place automatically whenever you required.

  Note: To mount any volume you required two resource on kubernetes.

1) PV : persistence volume => It contains storage related information, which you want provide for your container later.
                           => pv is cluster-wide object. it is always avalible of all namespace.
	1) storage URL
	2) type
	3) side
	4) AccessMode

    Note: cluster wide object. (means is not for single team, it is for full cluster. anyone can use this.)

2) PVC : presistence volume clean.  			==>>  It is a request of vomlume for deployment.


AccessMode:
===========
1) ReadwriteOnce: pv can mount at a time on the one node.( This restriction is node wise not pod wide.) means multiple pod can write data on same node. (Drop-back is it will not present data. data cloud be corrept due mutiple write operations)

  2) ReadwriteMany: one pv can be mount on multiple worker nodes and can write data multiple pods
  3) ReadOnlyMany : multiple worker nodes can mount with read-only access.
  4) ReadWriteOncePod :

The access modes are:

ReadWriteOnce – the volume can be mounted as read-write by a single node ... RWO
ReadOnlyMany – the volume can be mounted read-only by many nodes ... ROX
ReadWriteMany – the volume can be mounted as read-write by many nodes ... RWX


