IQ) Which one we need to create first. pv or pvc?
 	  a) In static provisioning => It does not matter, you could pvc request first also and you will get once pv avaliable.
 	  														you request will be in pending stage till not get the pv

      b) In Dynamic provising => pv will automatically get once you create a request, because it is dynamic.

Flow
====
Namespace => Pod => Deployment => PVC => PV => Storageserver(SAN/NAS)

Static provisioning
===================
Rclaime policy:
 1) Recycle: if pvc deleted then pv it avalible for new claim/team/use.(file lost)
 2) Retain : if pvc deleted then pv remain is same state(no data list)
 3) deleted: completely pv + data lost.

Note:
	=> create the nfs server and share the filesystem.
    => You can only create PV through file method.
	=> Static PV cannot be extend

